WEBVTT

00:01.835 --> 00:04.816
Previously on Mars.

00:05.746 --> 00:07.744
I will miss my sister,

00:07.751 --> 00:09.749
she's my heart and soul.

00:09.756 --> 00:11.729
For something
like this to work,

00:11.738 --> 00:12.790
it has to be personal.

00:12.793 --> 00:14.791
We had traveled
further than anyone ever

00:14.799 --> 00:16.747
had to get to Mars.

00:16.754 --> 00:19.739
But before we even
entered Mars's atmosphere

00:19.749 --> 00:21.731
it was like she was
trying to push us away.

00:21.739 --> 00:24.737
Retro
rockets about to fire.

00:26.764 --> 00:28.712
And
once we landed,

00:28.720 --> 00:29.744
she pushed even harder.

00:29.747 --> 00:30.796
What
is Ben's status?

00:32.768 --> 00:34.766
How far
did we overshoot?

00:34.773 --> 00:36.775
75.3 kilometers.

00:36.783 --> 00:38.719
Come on,
let's fix this.

00:38.726 --> 00:40.704
It's our guys up there.

00:40.714 --> 00:41.734
The
workshop module.

00:41.738 --> 00:42.766
What if they can
make it there?

00:42.770 --> 00:44.685
Live in it?

00:44.692 --> 00:47.698
They'd have a chance.

00:47.708 --> 00:48.765
Wheels 5 and 6 just locked.

00:48.769 --> 00:50.714
Suspension
system compromised.

00:50.721 --> 00:51.719
We have to walk.

00:51.722 --> 00:54.674
It's -35 degree.

00:54.685 --> 00:56.675
It will be -70 by nightfall.

00:56.682 --> 00:57.735
We'll freeze to
death out there.

00:57.739 --> 00:58.751
Jesus.

01:00.669 --> 01:01.697
Ben?

01:01.700 --> 01:04.660
Far off course,
we struggle to make our way

01:04.671 --> 01:05.744
to a temporary habitat.

01:05.748 --> 01:07.717
We
need to cut the suit.

01:07.724 --> 01:10.646
Fighting
just to stay alive.

01:10.658 --> 01:11.699
Dammit, Ben.

01:11.702 --> 01:13.721
Ben, stay with me.

01:13.729 --> 01:15.701
Come on, come on.

01:15.708 --> 01:20.646
Still our mission remained,
to find a safe haven for the

01:20.663 --> 01:22.678
first human
settlement on Mars.

01:27.691 --> 01:31.695
But getting there had
killed the best among us.

01:31.709 --> 01:36.617
I was in command now

01:36.635 --> 01:37.697
and I knew if we couldn't
find a permanent home

01:37.701 --> 01:42.667
in this place...

01:43.634 --> 01:48.629
the Mars Mission would die.

